<topic xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" id="toolbars" xsi:noNamespaceSchemaLocation="urn:oasis:names:tc:dita:xsd:topic.xsd:1.1">
  <title>Toolbars</title>
  <body>
    <p id="toolbars">Normally  the toolbars are located under the <xref href="menus.xml">menus</xref>. However, they can be moved to other positions, torn off or even hidden. All the commands performed through the toolbar buttons can also be performed through the <xref href="menus.xml">Menu bar</xref>.<ul>
        <li>To display/hide a toolbar, check/uncheck the <menucascade>
            <uicontrol>View</uicontrol>
            <uicontrol>Toolbars</uicontrol>
            <uicontrol>
              <varname>&lt;TOOLBAR NAME&gt;</varname>
            </uicontrol>
          </menucascade> menu item.</li>
        <li>
          <p>To change the position of a toolbar, click and drag it.</p>
        </li>
      </ul></p>
    <p id="types">The toolbars may differ depending on whether there is an opened document or not as well as on <xref href="document-type.xml">the type of the opened document</xref> and the <xref href="authoring-modes.xml">authoring mode</xref>.</p>
    <p>The possible toolbars are as follows:<ul>
        <li id="document-toolbar"><b>Document Toolbar</b> lets you <xref href="creating-new-document.xml">create</xref>/<xref href="opening-a-document-in-wysiwyg-mode.xml">open</xref>/<xref href="saving-document.xml">save</xref>/<xref href="printing-draft.xml">print</xref>/<xref href="publishing.xml">publish</xref> documents, <xref href="undo-redo-operations.xml">undo/redo operations</xref>, <xref href="copy-cut-paste.xml">cut/copy/paste</xref>, <xref href="find-replace.xml">find&amp;replace</xref>, <xref href="spellcheck.xml">check spelling</xref>, revalidate documents, call up help documentation and <xref href="using-element-help.xml">element help</xref>.<image href="document-toolbar.png" align="center" placement="break"/></li>
        <li id="xslt-toolbar"><b>XSLT Parameters Toolbar</b> lets you switch <xref href="xslt-parameter-sets.xml">XSLT Parameter Sets</xref>.<image href="xslt-parameters-toolbar.png" align="center" placement="break"/></li>
        <li id="element-toolbar"><b>Element Toolbar</b> lets you <xref href="inserting-element.xml">insert</xref>/<xref href="renaming-element.xml">rename</xref>/<xref href="splitting-element.xml">split</xref>/<xref href="joining-elements.xml">join</xref> elements and <xref href="editing-attributes.xml">edit elements&apos; attributes</xref>.<image href="element-toolbar.png" align="center" placement="break"/></li>
        <li id="insert-toolbar"><b>Insert Toolbar</b> lets you insert <xref href="entities.xml">internal and external entities</xref>, <xref href="insert-symbol-dialog.xml">symbols</xref>, <xref href="xinclude.xml">XInclude</xref>, <xref href="insert-comment-dialog.xml">comments</xref> and <xref href="insert-pi-dialog.xml">processing instructions</xref>.<image href="insert-toolbar.png" align="center" placement="break"/></li>
        <li id="zoom-toolbar"><b>Zoom Toolbar</b> lets you zoom documents.<image href="zoom-toolbar.png" align="center" placement="break"/></li>
        <li id="custom-content-toolbar"><b>Custom Content Toolbar</b> lets you create, edit and insert <xref href="custom-content-customization.xml">custom content</xref>.<image href="custom-content-toolbar.png" align="center" placement="break"/></li>
        <li id="table-toolbar"><b>Table Toolbar</b> lets you create and edit tables.<image href="table-toolbar.png" align="center" placement="break"/></li>
<!--<li><b>Redlining Toolbar</b> lets you <xref href="how-to-redline-doc.xml">redline documents</xref> and <xref href="revise-redline.xml">revise redlining</xref>.<image href="redlining-toolbar.png" align="center" placement="break"/></li>--><!--<li><b>DITA Toolbar</b> lets you insert topicrefs, local and external xrefs, conrefs, and related links.<image href="dita-toolbar.png" align="center" placement="break"/><note conref="references-in-dita-documents.xml#references-in-dita-documents/dita-usability-tools"/></li>-->      </ul></p>
  </body>
</topic>
